Leke Baiyewu, Abuja The Deputy Speaker, House of Representatives, Idris Wase, has congratulated the Sultan of Sokoto, Alhaji Muhammad Sa’ad Abubakar on his 63rd birthday anniversary. In a congratulatory message issued in Abuja on Saturday, Wase described the Sultan as an icon of peace, who through his spiritual counsel, brought peace and tolerance not only to Sokoto State but also the entire country. READ ALSO: Kyari, Adamu, others attend wedding of Sultan’s daughter The Deputy Speaker said, “His Eminence has over the years demonstrated both in words and in deeds that he is a true man of peace by always preaching unity, mutual understanding and peaceful coexistence among the diverse ethnic and religious groups in Nigeria. “As a spiritual leader and traditional ruler, you have over the years, distinguished yourself as an exemplary leader, traversing the length and breadth of the country, preaching peaceful coexistence and building bridges across religious and cultural divides.”